</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   SALT LAKE CITY (AP) -- Karl Malone scored 27 points and every Utah starter
reached double figures as the Jazz beat the Seattle SuperSonics 96-93 on Friday
night to win the first-round playoff series 3-2. John Stockton had 17 points and
hit two free throws with nine seconds remaining to preserve the victory. Utah
will play Portland in the Western Conference semifinals.
</P>
