<HEADLINE> Giants 5, Rockies 0  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- Joe Nathan combined with two relievers on a
three-hitter and J.T. Snow homered Friday night to give the San
Francisco Giants a 5-0 win over the Colorado Rockies.
</P>
<P>
   San Francisco, which broke open the game with a four-run eighth
inning, has won five straight and 11 of 13 following a 4-11 start.
The Giants stopped Colorado's three-game winning streak.
</P>
<P>
   Nathan (2-0) baffled a hot-hitting Colorado team, which came
into the game with a major league-leading .306 team average. The
Rockies had scored 72 runs in their last six games.
</P>
<P>
   Snow sliced an opposite-field liner to left in the second off
Masato Yoshii (1-3), who allowed two hits in seven innings,
retiring his last 15 batters.
</P>
<P>
   San Francisco got its eighth-inning runs on Bobby Estalella's
RBI double off Stan Belinda, Calvin Murray's two-run double off
Gabe White and Bill Mueller's run-scoring single.
</P>
<P>
   Nathan, clinging to a one-run lead, had walked the bases loaded
with two out in the seventh and went to a 3-1 count on Neifi Perez,
but Perez flied out to center on the next pitch.
</P>
<P>
   Nathan allowed two hits in seven innings, struck out five and
walked three. John Johnstone pitched a hitless eighth and Alan
Embree finished.
</P>
<P>
   Brian Hunter reached against Johnstone on a two-base fielding
error by Mueller at third base with two outs in the eighth, but
Mike Lansing hit a low liner to left fielder Barry Bonds, who went
down on his knees to make the catch.
Notes: Plate umpire Doug Eddings ejected two players, one from
each team, for extended arguments on called third strikes:
Colorado's Jeff Cirillo in the seventh and San Francisco's Jeff
Kent in the eighth. ... Giants manager Dusty Baker said OF Ellis
Burks is ready to rejoin the starting lineup, but kept him out
Friday night because of windy, 55-degree weather. He is expected to
make his first start in seven games Saturday. Burks has been
bothered by a strained left quadriceps. ... Rockies manager Buddy
Bell said OF Tom Goodwin probably will return to the starting
lineup Sunday. He strained his left abductor muscle Wednesday
against Montreal. ... Rockies RHP Rolando Arrojo will be activated
from the disabled list to start Saturday's game. It will be his
first career appearance against the Giants. ... It was the second
shutout of the year for San Francisco, which hasn't been blanked.
</P>
</TEXT>
