   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Looking every bit like championship material after a
two-game fling with self-doubt and mediocrity, the Los Angeles Lakers got a
dominant game from Shaquille O'Neal and turned it into a laugher early in the
third quarter as they steamrolled the Sacramento Kings 113-86 on Friday night in
the deciding game of the best-of-five first-round series. O'Neal outrebounded
the entire Sacramento team in the first half and finished with 32 points and 18
rebounds, while the rest of the team contributed steady offensive production and
superb defense.
