<HEADLINE> Canada 1, South Korea 0  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) -- Andrea Neil's header off a corner kick in
the 71st minute gave Canada a 1-0 victory over South Korea in the
semifinals of the U.S. Women's Cup on Friday night.
</P>
<P>
   Canada will play the United States, an 8-0 winner over Mexico,
in Sunday's championship game.
</P>
<P>
   The Americans have won the tournament all six years it has been
held.
</P>
<P>
   Neil's goal was set up by Sharolta Nonen's corner kick. Canada
was awarded the kick when Christine Sinclair missed a point-blank
shot in front of the goal, and after the ball bounced off keeper Ho
Jung Jung, a South Korean player booted it out of bounds.
</P>
<P>
   A little more than a minute after the goal, Canada goalkeeper
Nicole Wright made a diving save to prevent the tie. Wright made
another diving stop in the opening seconds of stoppage time.
</P>
</TEXT>
