<HEADLINE> Report: Fla. Senator Investigated  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MIAMI (AP) -- Florida officials are reviewing whether a state
senator broke state election laws by allegedly failing to report
thousands of dollars in campaign contributions and accepting cash
donations in excess of state election guidelines, a newspaper
reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Investigators who examined the bank records of state Sen. Alex
Diaz de la Portilla found evidence of 320 possible violations of
state law, according to a report obtained Friday by The Miami
Herald.
</P>
<P>
   The report, presented to the Florida Elections Commission this
week, says Diaz de la Portilla failed to report $158,195 in
contributions and three transfers totaling $67,000 from his
personal account, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
   Investigators also found that he may have violated state law by
accepting a cash contribution of $10,000, it said. State law
prohibits cash contributions in excess of $100.
</P>
<P>
   If the allegations are upheld, the commission could fine him a
record $843,999, the Herald reported. The allegations are also the
subject of a criminal investigation, it said.
</P>
<P>
   Calls to Diaz de la Portilla's Miami office were not immediately
returned Saturday.
</P>
</TEXT>
