<HEADLINE> Hospital Fire Kills Eight in Taiwan  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TAIPEI, Taiwan (AP) -- A fire blazed through a hospital before
dawn Saturday in eastern Taiwan, killing eight people, most of them
elderly patients, police reported.
</P>
<P>
   Another 18 people were injured, many of them too ill to walk,
and were rescued by firefighters from the burning five-story
hospital in Ilan, 70 miles southeast of Taipei, police said.
</P>
<P>
   It took more than 100 firefighters two hours to extinguish the
fire.
</P>
<P>
   Among those who died in the blaze were a 90-year-old woman and
her 23-year-old granddaughter tending to her, both of whom died of
smoke inhalation.
</P>
<P>
   Police did not know yet what caused the fire, had not ruled out
the possibility of arson.
</P>
</TEXT>
