<HEADLINE> TV's 'Frasier' To Star in 'Macbeth'  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Kelsey Grammer is making himself at home in New
York City this summer so he can play the lead in ''Macbeth'' on
Broadway.
</P>
<P>
   The ''Frasier'' star told the New York Daily News he's a stage
actor in his heart.
</P>
<P>
   ''Stage is my favorite,'' he said. ''But I've been away from
that. And it's harder to make a living at that.''
</P>
<P>
   Grammer just wrapped the film ''15 Minutes,'' in which he stars
as a tabloid journalist opposite Robert De Niro and Ed Burns.
</P>
</TEXT>
