<HEADLINE> Lewis Stalker Is Arrested Again  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LAS VEGAS, Nev. (AP) -- A man who served a prison sentence for
stalking Jerry Lewis is in custody again.
</P>
<P>
   Gary Benson, 56, who completed his Nevada prison term in
September, was arrested Friday in Wyoming, the FBI said.
</P>
<P>
   According to the agency, Lewis received an April 5 letter that
said: ''Dear Jerry. Your dead. Your friend, Gary Benson.''
</P>
<P>
   Benson, of Sheridan, Wyo., was charged with one count of
aggravated stalking and one count of violation of an extended
protective order.
</P>
<P>
   Benson pleaded guilty in May 1995 to aggravated stalking, a
felony. He initially was sentenced to probation, but was ordered to
prison for continuing to harass Lewis.
</P>
</TEXT>
