</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Reggie Miller and Jalen Rose each scored 40 points as
the Indiana Pacers routed the Philadelphia 76ers 108-91 today in Game 1 of their
Eastern Conference semifinal series. Miller, who set a franchise playoff record
with 41 points as Indiana beat Milwaukee 96-95 in Game 5 of their first-round
series on Thursday night, shot Indiana ahead to stay with 16 points in the
opening period.
</P>
