<HEADLINE> Southern Miss Pitcher Sets Record  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   HATTIESBURG, Miss. (AP) -- Southern Mississippi pitcher Courtney
Blades set an NCAA record with 1,643 career strikeouts as she
struck out 16 batters in winning both ends of a doubleheader
against South Florida on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Blades, a senior, passed California's Michelle Granger, who had
1,640 strikeouts from 1989-93.
</P>
<P>
   Blades struck out 11 in just five innings as the Lady Eagles won
the first game of the doubleheader 9-0. She got five more in three
innings to lead Southern Miss to a 10-2 victory and the sweep.
</P>
<P>
   Last week, Blades broke her own single-season strikeout record
of 497 set last season. She now has 516 strikeouts and is 42-5 this
season.
</P>
</TEXT>
