<HEADLINE> Leafs' Clark Misses Game Vs. Devils  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TORONTO (AP) -- Toronto Maple Leafs left wing Wendel Clark missed
Saturday's Game 5 against the New Jersey Devils due to an
undisclosed injury.
</P>
<P>
   Clark was seen wearing a bandage across his midsection Wednesday
night, following Toronto's 3-2 victory that tied the best-of-seven
Eastern Conference second-round series 2-2.
</P>
<P>
   After being a healthy scratch for Toronto's first four playoff
games, Clark had played in the last six, recording a goal and an
assist. His assist was a critical one, setting up Darcy Tucker's
game-winning goal in Game 1 against the Devils.
</P>
<P>
   Fans at the Air Canada Centre booed when it was announced that
Clark -- one of Toronto's more beloved athletes -- would not play.
</P>
<P>
   The Maple Leafs inserted Adam Mair into the lineup in Clark's
place. Mair has appeared in four playoff games this season,
including Games 2 and 3 against the Devils.
</P>
<P>
   Toronto defenseman Gerald Diduck missed his second straight game
with a suspected leg injury.
</P>
<P>
   The Devils got a boost as second-line forward Sergei Brylin
returned to the lineup after hurting his knee in Game 2 of New
Jersey's opening-round series against Florida.
</P>
</TEXT>
