<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lukas Has Bad Derby Outing  </HEADLINE>
By HARRY KING, AP Sports Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOUISVILLE, Ky. (AP) -- A year after winning the Kentucky Derby
for the third time in five years, trainer D. Wayne Lukas was a flop
Saturday as his starters finished 12th, 15th and 17th in the
19-horse field.
</P>
<P>
   ''They ran flat for whatever reason,'' said Lukas, who has won
four Derbys and has started a record 38 horses since 1981. ''There
is always an explanation of some kind. We've been there before and
had that situation, so we'll see.
</P>
<P>
   ''I was disappointed in all three of them because they all
trained so well for the race. But it's a horse race, and sometimes
it's unexplainable.''
</P>
<P>
   Lukas had particularly high hopes for Blue Grass winner High
Yield, who finished 15th, two dozen lengths behind winner Fusaichi
Pegasus.
</P>
<P>
   Prior to the Derby, he pointed to High Yield's 12 races, almost
$1.2 million in earnings, three Grade I victories and the presence
of jockey Pat Day -- the king of the Churchill Downs track.
</P>
<P>
   ''I had a good trip, I just didn't have any horse,'' Day said.
''He warmed up nice and I thought he would be all right, but he
never showed any enthusiasm. He was just going through the motions.
I was in position at the half-mile pole, but I didn't have any
horse.''
</P>
<P>
   The Lukas-trained Exchange Rate, the longest shot in the field
at almost 60-1, showed some speed, but faded to 12th. Lukas'
Commendable, who had won only a maiden race in six starts, was
never in contention and beat two in the 19-horse field.
</P>
<P>
   Lukas said he has no immediate plans for any of the three.
</P>
<P>
   Lukas won the Derby with Winning Colors in 1988, Thunder Gulch
in 1995, Grindstone in 1996 and Charismatic last year.
</P>
<P>
   Ben Jones holds the record of training six Derby winners, but he
only started 11 horses.
</P>
<P>
   Lukas, 65, said earlier this week that his goal is to saddle 10
Derby winners.
</P>
<P>
   ''The record is there,'' he said. ''We'll shoot at it. But as
long as we're going to be in the business, we might as well win
10.''
</P>
<P>
   Often, he is criticized for running horses that don't seem to
belong in the race. He has admitted that the Derby is important to
him, but even more important to his clients.
</P>
<P>
   ''They want to play in this arena, and I try to put them
there,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Lukas also entered three horses in 1983, 1987, 1990 and 1995 and
five horses in 1996. The '83 group finished fifth, ninth and 20th;
the '87 contingent was 10th, 13th and 16th; and the '90 bunch
finished seventh, 10th and 11th.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-05-06-00 1946 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
