<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rangers Purchase Green's Contract  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ARLINGTON, Texas (AP) -- The Texas Rangers purchased the contract
of outfielder Scarborough Green from Oklahoma of the Pacific Coast
League prior to Saturday's game against the Oakland Athletics.
</P>
<P>
   To make room for Green, Texas optioned shortstop Kelly
Dransfeldt to Oklahoma. To make room on the 40-man roster, Texas
designated RedHawks catcher Cesar King for assignment.
</P>
<P>
   Green was hitting .313 with one homer, 10 RBIs and 14 stolen
bases in 27 games for Oklahoma. He has played 38 major league games
with St. Louis and Texas during the last three seasons with a .159
average. Green hit .308 in 18 games in four stints with the Rangers
last year.
</P>
<P>
   Dransfeldt was recalled from Oklahoma on Thursday. He made one
appearance, Thursday against Tampa Bay, going 0-for-1 after coming
in as a pinch hitter.
</P>
<P>
   King hit .143 with seven RBIs in 13 games at Oklahoma.
</P>
</TEXT>
