<HEADLINE> Nineteen-year-old sailor drowns in pre-dawn boating accident  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   MALTA RIDGE, N.Y. (AP) -- Six people were rescued after a boat
capsized on Saratoga Lake at about 3 a.m. Saturday, awakening
neighbors with the din. A 19-year-old Naval sailor from Indiana is
presumed drowned and alcohol is believed to have played a role in
the incident.
</P>
<P>
   State police say that six U.S. Navy sailors and a female friend
attempted to cross Saratoga Lake in a 14-foot rowboat, apparently
after drinking beer at a nearby residence.
</P>
<P>
   About halfway across the lake, police say, one of the boaters
entered the water. When he attempted to climb back into the boat,
it capsized, spilling the remaining passengers into 51-degree
water. Attempts to get to shore by clinging to the boat and kicking
failed.
</P>
<P>
   One boater, Aaron Wayne Binkerd of Indiana, was apparently
overcome by the frigid water and drifted away from the others, who
were rescued by nearby residents and the Malta Ridge Fire
Department.
</P>
<P>
   State police and environmental conservation officers as well as
teams from the Malta Ridge fire department and both Warren and
Saratoga counties were unable to locate Binkerd's body Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   The search was to resume Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   All others in the accident were treated for hypothermia and
released from Saratoga Hospital.
</P>
<P>
   The six sailors were from the Knolls Atomic Power
Laboratory\Kesserling site about seven miles away in West Milton.
The lab conducts research and development for the design and
operation of naval nuclear propulsion plants.
</P>
</TEXT>
